      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $a_1, \\dots, a_n \\in \\Z$ distincts.",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(a_1, \\dots, a_n \\in \\Z\\)</span>\ndistincts.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "884438d7-ddde-472a-b2ab-3aabc4b4e6a6",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $(X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) - 1$ est irr{\\'e}ductible dans ${\\Z[X]}$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) -\n1\\)</span> est irr<span>é</span>ductible dans <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\({\\Z[X]}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "fbd57958-a88b-4771-b4e3-78ab41aab597",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Si $P = QR$ alors $Q(a_i)R(a_i) = -1  \\Rightarrow  Q(a_i) = -R(a_i) = \\pm1$,\n    donc $Q+R$ a $n$ racines, donc est nul, et $P = -Q^2$~:\n    contradiction pour $x \\to \\infty$.",
        "html": "<p>Si <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P = QR\\)</span> alors <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Q(a_i)R(a_i) = -1  \\Rightarrow  Q(a_i) = -R(a_i) =\n\\pm1\\)</span>, donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q+R\\)</span> a <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span> racines, donc est nul, et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(P = -Q^2\\)</span> : contradiction pour <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(x \\to \\infty\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "22926958-8499-4708-8a8e-4503836fd167",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "M{\\^e}me question avec $(X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n) + 1$, $n$ impair.",
        "html": "<p>M<span>ê</span>me question avec <span class=\"math inline\">\\((X-a_1)\n\\dots (X-a_n) + 1\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\)</span>\nimpair.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "e1aff985-ab9b-4e34-9a60-252799115c20",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "M{\\^e}me raisonnement : $P = Q^2$, donc\n    $Q^2-1 = (Q-1)(Q+1) = (X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n)$.\n    \\par\n    On r{\\'e}partit les facteurs entre $Q-1$ et $Q+1$ : $n = 2p$, contradiction.",
        "html": "<p>M<span>ê</span>me raisonnement : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P =\nQ^2\\)</span>, donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(Q^2-1 = (Q-1)(Q+1) =\n(X-a_1) \\dots (X-a_n)\\)</span>.</p>\n<p>On r<span>é</span>partit les facteurs entre <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Q-1\\)</span> et <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(Q+1\\)</span> : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n =\n2p\\)</span>, contradiction.</p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
